# What is this?
For rookie at may be frustruating to bootstrap first react project. That's bocause React uses a lot of other tools, like transpilers, packge managers etc.
But there is a fast way to start your first React project, and after you finish it, it would be easy to deploy.
So create-react-app is a simple ready made enviroment for your react projects.

# 1 Install Node.js
[Node.js](https://nodejs.org) is a Java Script runtime. It goes with a very handy tool called NPM (node packet manager), with npm you dont need to download
Java Script libraries and their depences manually, npm will do it for you. To install Node, just download installer from https://nodejs.org

# 2 Install create-react-app on your computer
Now open your OS terminal and install create-react-app, just execute this command
```sh
npm install -g create-react-app
```
Npm will do the rest.

# 3 Set your project
Now you can open your projects folder via terminal
```sh
cd [path-to-your-folder]
```
And create new react project here
```sh
create-react-app my-app
```
It will create a directory called `my-app` inside the current folder.

# 4 Start your developement server
create-react-app goes with build in server for fast development
Just execute 
```sh
cd my-app
npm start
```
It starts the server on your [http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000)

You can start you worck with React

# 5 Deploy your project
After you finish, create-react-app will help you to deploy your project
```sh
npm run build
```

And your ptoject is ready for deployment.

## After you get familiar with this handy tools, feel free to read more about create-react-app, how it works etc.
## [create-react-app page](https://github.com/facebookincubator/create-react-app/blob/master/README.md)

